cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): The paper focuses on analyzing the early spreading patterns of memes in social networks to predict their future popularity. This falls under the scope of social and information networks. 

2. cs.SD (Software Engineering): The paper proposes and analyzes a comprehensive set of features to develop an accurate model for predicting the success of memes. This involves software engineering techniques for feature engineering and model development. 

3. cs.SOC (Computational Social Science): The paper uses computational methods to study the predictability of successful memes in social networks. This falls under the scope of computational social science. 

4. cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity): The paper may also fall under the scope of cybersecurity as it involves analyzing the spread of memes in social networks, which can have implications for online security and privacy. 

5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper involves analyzing the characteristics of adoption time series to predict the success of memes. This falls under the scope of information retrieval, which deals with the organization and retrieval of information from large datasets.
